00:03:18.980 --> 00:03:24.430
Photography being my main hobby, this new
option interests me quite a bit.

00:03:24.430 --> 00:03:28.780
Professional photo, a title like that just
screams color accuracy.

00:03:28.780 --> 00:03:31.880
The option in this same spot used to be called
Neutral.

00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:37.510
I'm not 100% sure if the color has changed,
but I always thought Neutral looked very washed

00:03:37.510 --> 00:03:42.690
out and that's why I never used that mode
even though the colors seemed a lot more accurate.

00:03:42.690 --> 00:03:47.599
But now, it seems more saturated and I'm happy
leaving it at professional photo now.

00:03:47.599 --> 00:03:50.470
Much better than Dynamic or standard in my
opinion.

00:03:50.470 --> 00:03:56.099
As for color, accuracy, I wouldn't say you
can use the Note 2 now as a color calibration

00:03:56.099 --> 00:04:02.030
tool, but I do think the colors are a little
bit better, so it's a big improvement in my

00:04:02.030 --> 00:04:03.030
book.

