The rest I'll talk about today are just cosmetic
changes.

00:04:06.019 --> 00:04:11.079
The notification bar is a transparent gradient...Your
carrier logo may show up on the top left.

00:04:11.079 --> 00:04:12.079
At least it did for me.

00:04:12.079 --> 00:04:14.430
The smart stay eye icon is always there.

00:04:14.430 --> 00:04:19.010
It just becomes highlight for a split second
while it's checking to see if you're there.

00:04:19.010 --> 00:04:22.650
If you don't have Smart Stay enabled, I recommend
you use it.

00:04:22.650 --> 00:04:24.620
It's a great feature.

00:04:24.620 --> 00:04:29.950
Smart stay has changed slightly on how it
works on Android 4.3.

00:04:29.950 --> 00:04:33.970
It used to be that, if it didn't see you for
the first time, it dims the screen and checks

00:04:33.970 --> 00:04:38.780
to see if you're there again before turning
off the screen 5 seconds later.

00:04:38.780 --> 00:04:42.600
Now, once it goes dim, it does not check to
see if you're there.

00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:46.360
You have to touch the screen in 5 seconds
before it turns off.

00:04:46.360 --> 00:04:50.100
At first I didn't like this, but it makes
sense.

00:04:50.100 --> 00:04:54.220
When you see it go dim, you normally would
just tap on the screen anyway.

00:04:54.220 --> 00:04:58.290
And not wait around in front of the camera
for a few seconds to make it go brighter again.

00:04:58.290 --> 00:05:02.750
I think this will save some battery as well.

